===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''deeth'', from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|deaþ|dēaþ}}, from {{proto|Germanic}} *''dauþuz'' (compare West Frisian {{term|dead|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|dood}}, German {{term|Tod}}, Swedish {{term|död}}), from {{proto|Indo-European}} *''dʰautus''. More at [[die]].

